assignmentevaluator.evaluationHelpers.executors.programlevel.RunTestExecutor
public class RunTestExecutor extends assignmentevaluator.evaluationHelpers.executors.programlevel.ProgramTestExecutor
Class that represents an executor for running program-level tests on assignments. This class specifically handles the execution of tests that check whether the assignment runs correctly (e.g., whether the program produces an exit code 0).

  • Method Details

    • handlePass

      public void handlePass()
      Handles the case where the test passes. If the assignment runs successfully and returns exit code 0, the marks are awarded and feedback is set indicating that the assignment ran successfully.
      Specified by:
      handlePass in class assignmentevaluator.evaluationHelpers.executors.programlevel.ProgramTestExecutor

    • handleFailure

      public void handleFailure(org.junit.platform.launcher.listeners.TestExecutionSummary testExecutionSummary)
      Handles the case where the test fails. If the assignment fails to run, this method processes the test execution summary, providing details on which test failed and the reason for the failure.
      Specified by:
      handleFailure in class assignmentevaluator.evaluationHelpers.executors.programlevel.ProgramTestExecutor
      Parameters:
      testExecutionSummary - The summary of the test execution, containing failure details

    • executeTest

      public void executeTest()
      Executes the test by setting up the test details and running the test. It checks the execution summary to determine whether the assignment ran successfully or if there were any failures. If the test passes, it invokes the handlePass() method; otherwise, it invokes handleFailure(TestExecutionSummary).
      Specified by:
      executeTest in class assignmentevaluator.evaluationHelpers.executors.TestExecutor
